# History: planning-unmerged-parent-contract-compile-smoke-gate

## v1.2.0 (2026-07-02)

Amended after authoring the plan for ProjectOdyssey issue #5526 — a
**validation-only** child issue that runs a CIFAR-10 one-epoch training
script (produced by unmerged parent #5525), captures a log, and asserts a
loss-decrease criterion. The plan was authored without running
`gh issue view 5525 --comments` and without grep-verifying paths in the
current tree; every entrypoint path, CLI flag, batch log format, smoke-test
path, container invocation form, and wall-clock budget was inferred from
the issue's title/body prose.

The v1.1.0 skill already covered "unmerged parent + approved-plan
contract + compile-smoke gate" for CODE-CHANGE child issues. v1.2.0
extends the same discipline to the **validation-only** sub-case, where
the child does not modify code but runs a script produced by the parent
and asserts a scalar criterion. Six sub-patterns added:

1. **Log-parser sanity check** — a bash wrapper that runs `mojo run
   <script>` and pipes into a Python (or Mojo) summarizer can exit 0
   (script succeeded) while the summarizer produces a garbage result on
   a format mismatch. Mandate a `parsed N > 0` sanity check with `raise
   SystemExit(1)` on failure and `PARSED n=<N> expected=<E> format=<pattern>`
   diagnostic. Without this: false-negative NOGO (or false-positive GO
   if `nan < nan` masks the empty-list case).

2. **Smoothed-trend loss-decrease criterion** — a "mean of first 10% of
   batches vs mean of last 10%" comparison is pathological on short/noisy
   runs: a legitimately monotonically-decreasing epoch can still fail if
   the last decile plateaus above the first decile due to noise. Prefer a
   linear-fit slope `b < 0` as the primary criterion; widen the comparison
   window (first third vs last third) as a fallback. Cite the number of
   samples the criterion is asserted on.

3. **Assumption Mapping for Mechanical Re-Plan** — for validation-only
   child issues, include a dedicated table (`Assumption | Cited As |
   File/line to fix once parent merges | Verify With`) so re-planning
   after the parent PR merges is a mechanical find-and-replace, not a
   re-read of the whole plan. Every row is either sourced from the
   parent's approved-plan comment line-anchored, or flagged unverified.

4. **Container-network preflight** — a validation script that runs inside
   a container (`podman`, `just shell`, `docker`) inherits the container's
   network namespace. Dataset auto-download may be blocked by the container's
   egress policy. Either verify the network policy, pre-stage data on the
   host and bind-mount, or add a preflight: `if [ ! -d "$DATA_DIR" ]; then
   echo "PLAN: data not present" >&2; exit 2; fi`. Also verify the
   `just shell -c '<cmd>'` invocation form before planning on it.

5. **Gitignored-artifact attachment** — `logs/`, `runs/`, `checkpoints/` are
   commonly gitignored. `git add logs/<file>.log` silently no-ops and the PR
   ships without evidence. Plan artifact attachment up front: (a)
   `git add -f logs/<specific-file>`, (b) copy to `docs/evidence/`, or (c)
   attach via `gh pr comment --body-file`. Specify which of the three,
   with the exact command, in the plan.

6. **Wall-clock heuristic without benchmark evidence** — a "60-minute
   wall-clock threshold, `MAX_BATCHES=200` fallback" pair is not a fact.
   Either cite a benchmark (prior epoch on target hardware, parent PR's
   smoke test seconds/batch) or explicitly label the numbers as
   "heuristic, no benchmark data — reviewer should override if their
   hardware differs." Both paths are valid; hiding the guess is not.

Failed-attempts table grew from 13 rows to 21 (added attempts 14-21
capturing the validation-only sub-case patterns as concrete plan-time
misses on the ProjectOdyssey #5526 R0 plan).

Also added: (a) an "Assumption Mapping for Mechanical Re-Plan"
copy-paste template; (b) a Python log-parser sanity check snippet;
(c) a smoothed-trend (linear-fit slope) loss-decrease criterion snippet;
(d) container preflight + gitignored-artifact attachment copy-paste
covering the three attachment options.

## v1.1.0 (2026-07-02)

Amended after a NOGO→R1 revision on ProjectOdyssey #5516 revealed that
**4-of-4** reviewer-flagged unverified APIs were WRONG on first `Read`:

1. `randn` — R0 assumed `mean=/std=` kwargs. On-disk
   (`src/projectodyssey/tensor/tensor_creation.mojo:531`) signature is
   `def randn(shape: List[Int], dtype: DType, seed: Int = 0) raises -> AnyTensor`
   — N(0,1) only. R0 test would not compile.
2. `cross_entropy` — R0 assumed integer class-index labels. On-disk
   (`src/projectodyssey/core/loss.mojo:260-292`) targets MUST be one-hot,
   same shape as logits. R0 would silently produce wrong loss (no dtype
   guard raise). Fix: `one_hot_encode` from
   `src/projectodyssey/data/formats/idx_loader.mojo:246`.
3. `AnyTensor.store[dtype]` — RIGHT (`any_tensor.mojo:1499`) but
   correct-by-coin-flip: `.set` also exists at line 860 with ~12
   dtype overloads.
4. `extract_batch_pair` — RIGHT
   (`src/projectodyssey/data/batch_utils.mojo:76-78` returns
   `Tuple[AnyTensor, AnyTensor]`) but unverified in R0.

Primary added learning: **When a reviewer NOGOs a plan for unverified
APIs, `Read` each flagged API's source line NOW and revise every
assumption that was wrong — do NOT add a "verify later" step to the
plan.** Assume 100% wrong-rate on cited-but-unread APIs until proven
otherwise on disk.

Sub-patterns added (all triggered from the same "planning revision
after NOGO for a Mojo/ProjectOdyssey issue" context):

- **Two-tier convergence assertion** — hard floor
  `assert_true(loss_final < loss_initial)` asserted BEFORE the
  issue-prescribed `< 0.95 * loss_initial` check, so failure logs
  distinguish "no decrease" from "insufficient decrease." Never
  weaken the issue-prescribed threshold; mitigate on data/hyperparams
  side (samples×3.2, class-mean bias×2, warm-up epoch).
- **Same-line coordination hazard on rebase** — when two concurrent
  PRs edit the identical line, rebase detects the pre-fixed line as
  an empty hunk; drop it with `git commit --amend --no-edit`, no
  merge conflict.
- **Cross-file caller grep before signature change** —
  `grep -rn 'fname(' --include='*.mojo'` to prove no other file
  calls the per-example function before changing its signature.
- **Smoke-run the example's own `main()`** — a test file that
  imports from the example proves compile but NOT that `main()`
  runs end-to-end (arg parser, dataset loader, checkpoint path
  can all break independently).
- **Name-collision with overload family trap** — `.set` (12 overloads,
  `any_tensor.mojo:860`) and `.store[dtype]` (parametric, line 1499)
  both exist on `AnyTensor`. Two-of-a-kind API names on the same
  type require explicit grep of BOTH forms before citation.

Failed-attempts table grew from 7 rows to 13 (added attempts 8-13
capturing the above patterns as concrete R0-vs-R1 misses).

## v1.0.0 (2026-07-02)

Initial capture from ProjectOdyssey issue #5516 plan review (parent
issue #5515 unmerged; only an approved-plan comment existed). Seven
learnings distilled from six unverified-API assumptions plus a
same-line-coordination hazard.

Merged in PR
